The course examines the historical development and change of English, Old, Middle and New English texts are read and analyzed;an overview of the main variants of English in the world, the spread and the future of English is given.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To introduce the main features of the development of English at different stages of history and the variants of English used in the world and their features.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1) knows the basic stages of development of the English language and the language changes that have taken place in them; 2) can name and explain the reasons for the development of the English language and its connection with historical events; 3) knows and is able to name linguistic features and forms from different stages of development (Old, Middle and New English); 4) can distinguish and read texts from different stages of development (Old, Middle and New English). 5) be aware of the English language variants used in the world and their peculiarities; 6) can distinguish between different English language variants
